<div style="background: lightblue; font-style: italic;">
   <h2><center>Getting OneTime</center></h2>
</div>

<p>I recommend OneTime <strong>1XVERSION</strong> right now.  When
development on 2XVERSION is complete, this page will be updated.</p>

<ul>

<li><p>Download the full package as a .tar.gz file:
    <a href="onetime-1XVERSION.tar.gz"
       >onetime-1XVERSION.tar.gz</a> 
    (or <a href="onetime-2XVERSION.tar.gz"
       >onetime-2XVERSION.tar.gz</a>).<br/>
    (This is the recommended way for non-Windows.)</p></li>

<li><p>Download the full package as a zip file:
    <a href="onetime-1XVERSION.zip"
       >onetime-1XVERSION.zip</a>
    (or <a href="onetime-2XVERSION.zip"
       >onetime-2XVERSION.zip</a>).<br/>
    (This is the recommended way for Windows.)</p></li>

<li><p>You could just download the <a href="onetime-1XVERSION"
    >standalone 1XVERSION script</a> (or <a href="onetime"
    >2XVERSION script</a>) directly, if you don't want the README, the
    test suite, or other incidental files.</p></li>

<li><p>OneTime 1.x is packaged in <a href="http://debian.org/">Debian
    GNU/Linux</a> now.  If you run the "testing" distribution of
    Debian or higher, do
    <tt>'sudo&nbsp;apt-get&nbsp;update&nbsp;&amp;&amp;&nbsp;sudo&nbsp;apt-get&nbsp;install&nbsp;onetime'</tt>
    (or the equivalent in your preferred package management
    interface).<br />
    <em>Note that as of Nov 2013, the version of OneTime packaged
    in Debian is somewhat behind the upstream release.  We'll try to
    get Debian updated soon after OneTime 2.0 comes out.</em></p></li>

<li><p>Gitorious: <a href="https://gitorious.org/onetime"
                  >gitorious.org/onetime</a></p></li>

<li><p>GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/kfogel/OneTime"
               >github.com/kfogel/OneTime</a></p></li>
</ul>

